{
  "text": "The diffractograms of the 23 green necklace beads of Castillejo del Bonete match files 25-18 (a mixture of variscite and metavariscite with a quartz intergrowth and high levels of Fe). There were differences in peak intensity and minor movements in the main diffraction planes towards greater and lesser angles with no clear pattern to said file. This could indicate mineralogical differences in structure [CITATION_1] i.e., secondary or minor minerals, or an amorphous, noncrystalline material in the beds' raw material.",
  "citation_candidates": [
